reviews.text: Amazing concert venue. I have been going to this venue for years and I'm always amazed by the ornate detail of this theater. Great space and easy to get in and out of. Great places to grab something to eat and drink nearby as well. Weather it be comedy shows, music or plays, the Palace is a great spot to enjoy.

Beautiful building in downtown Albany. Saw Justin Moore last night.. Pretty clean. Sticky floors but that's what happens when drinks spill. Would definitely go to another show there. I didn't think any seat in the house was a bad seat. We had 10th row. But I also went to back for a breather and those seats weren't bad either.

This theatre is absolutely gorgeous and sounds great. The staff is awesome and concession costs are reasonable with a decent selection of canned craft brews available for $8. I highly recommend seeing any show here.

Attended a concert here with my daughter. Small venue made it seem very personal. I don't believe there was a bad seat in the house! The baroque style 
interior was beautiful. Depending on the band, I would definitely make the four hour drive to return to the Palace Theatre.

I really enjoyed seeing my favorite band at this venue. The architecture in this place is beautiful. The sound is great. The staff was kind.  Seating for the event was first come first sat. I will definitely return for a show in the future.\mm/

Wonderful place.  Beautiful building and great history as well.  My goodness all the displays could go on forever and forever.  We took so many pictures and the museum keeps changing so it's always interesting.  It's best to go early because there is so much to see.  Great for all ages and see if your local library provides day passes.  Manchester did a few years ago. Call both locations to confirm.  Would go definitely go again.  Plus the children's science museum was next door as well.
It was a wonderful experience. The students learned an awful of important information. Excellent tour guides. Activities were great. Thank you do much.
What a great little museum! Lots of interesting exhibits packed into a small area. Definitely a must while visting Manchester  and appreciating its history.
Great place... Few cities our size could have a museum like this, which bodes much for Manchester... History always has something new to say

Fine museum with mostly static displays through the history of NH and Manchester. I grew up in Manchester so lots of interesting things.  They have interesting world war 1 exhibit.  Low cost.  I joined as member as planning on attending Feb presentation on The Ledge.
Are you looking for *real* Mexican food?  Look no further.  Neighborhood is improving, but the food is top notch!

I am a California girl that is always in search of REAL mexican food since I moved here 10 years ago.  This is the second place that I have been that it true authentic and DELICIOUS.  The other is in Waltham, Mass
The ONLY good mexican food in NH. Moved here from AZ (where mexican foods on every corner) & this is the only place that reminds me of the food at home!

Excellent food.  The Mudslides are famous there and now I know why.  The fried scallops and clams were the best.  The oils used to fry them and the light coating made them incredible.  Service was great too.  Overall an A+ experience
We always enjoy this restaurant.  Mostly an older crowd. Very good food. Excellent  service and reasonable prices. Lots of parking.. well worth a visit.

I really enjoyed myself here at this restaurant. There is lots of room and a comfortable atmosphere. The waitress who served us was very friendly. We had a small problem with our order and she fixed it without any complaints whatsoever. I was grateful to find that the restaurant has a gluten-free menu. I enjoyed a delicious salad and some fries (which they cautioned me were not technically gluten free). The portions were very generous.

Apparently the chicken fingers are to die for but I don't eat chicken so I can't speak to that. My blackened Caribbean salmon with mashed potatoes was amazing though! Nice place. Well rounded menu. Great place whether if you have kids or not.

A New Hampshire staple. Friendly staff. High quality American food for a fair price. Chicken tenders are the best I've ever had. Take my family here every time they visit. You're going to want to try the ice cream too!

Beautiful little spot. Very comfy and relaxing you can tell its owned by a older couple. And I mean that in a good way. The food/desserts are tasty and well priced. I would recommend to anyone trying something different. The only blemish would be the hours (7-3) which does not give much eating time for 9-5 workers who intact would miss lunch/dinner times altogether.
Quaint comfortable, friendly and affordable great food and best desserts.
Great service, decent portion but nothing spectacular.

Love the goulash and schnitzel that Lalas has. Definitely have to try the reasonably priced desserts, too, they're twice as delicious as they look! The owner really treats you like a guest in his home, service has always been excellent the many times I've been here.

Best priced coffee on elm st. (Less than $2).
Homemade soup daily! Warm and welcoming.

Have been here a few times...The last time was Last night for my 36th wedding anniversary! What a treat! The service is excellent, food is great portions right on! Started with the Cheese fondue Appetizer and ended with the Chocolate Fondue Dessert...This restaurant never disappoints! Drinks are excellent and priced fairly you will enjoy your evening here and you will not have to take a second mortgage if you have more than one drink!!!!!!

Yummy breakfast! Cuban egg sandwich rocks! The good vibes organic coffee was a perfect compliment. I love the idea that I can go to Scotts restaurant any hour and order a cocktail or breakfast if the mood strikes! Kahlua with my coffee made this perfect meal 5stars for me. O yes...try the crepes with real maple syrup.

I have been enjoying Unwined for 11 years.  It is very relaxed but comes with all the benefits of fine dining.   The pricing is a good value.  The drinks are always generous and the food portions are large.  The service flower on each table is a great addition to the restaurant.  When you pull the flower out of the vase, someone is always at the table to help in a timely manner.   If the flower is not out of the vase, we are not constantly interrupted by a server.  It is a great place to go and kill a few hours without feeling rushed.  The atmosphere is very cozy and well decorated.

Big fan of Unwine'd!  The Chef/Owner is a master and artist.  I have dined here dozens of times and always have had excellent experiences.  The staff is trained incredibly well and on many occasions the Chef himself came out to talk to us.  Awesome!

Was 5 stars before it tacked on key west and changed the menu.  First time years ago was amazing and the flower service made the experience intimate and enjoyable.  Last time going the flower was ignored completely and we were waited on as if in an applebees.  Great concept ruined by an uninspired attempt at innovation.

Proper honest pub with a warm welcome. Good food sensible priced, good bear and lovely staff. The atmosphere is really friendly and welcomes dogs which is always a good sign as to the relaxing feel to a country pub. I've been hear serveal times and it has been like this. The landlord is always engaging in conversation and will ask if everything was ok and not because he's paying you lip service, this also carries through with there hard working staff.

Lovely pub but they had a power cut just before we arrived. Staff were stressed and politeness went out the window demanding cash to pay for the drinks I had just ordered. If they had let me know about the power cut before I ordered the drinks I could have had the choice to stay or move on.

Good value for your money. The staff are very friendly and courteous. The pub on the outside gives the impression of an old Inn. But inside its resonably modern. It's worth a visit, E will deffinatly go again.
Lovely local pub. Visited in a Sunday afternoon for a drink after a walk and ended up dining there too. Lovely food, people and atmosphere.

Lovely little place, the food was ok just like any normal pub. Nice and clean toilets, sweet little section for us to eat in. I ordered the bbq ribs which were really nice, my partner had sausage and mash which he wasn’t too keen on but it was still nice, followed by a brownie which he really enjoyed. Not from the area, live by the seaside in Kent and thought the prices were going to leave a dent in my bank account but it was actually quite cheap. Really lovely staff, was staying in the Nutfield hotel and I wish the staff were more like the ones at the pub! Would definitely return if I’m ever in that area again.

Not impressed.  Walked in as the only people in the waiting area...  we gave them our party size and waited.  Several staff acknowledged us.  Then we realized others were coming in and being seated.  
Apparently no one put us down to be seated...as we stood in front of them not one person wondered why we were there?  After mentioning it, we're seated in a reserved table immediately.
Steak was over done.  Waiter forgot my drink. 
We wont go back.  Texas road house is better.  Its busy and loud and they still get it right. 👍

I went in last night and had a fabulous dinner and service was incredible (had Tammy as our server). The food is always great there! I was so happy to see that the manager Bill was back. His friendly way with people is what makes this particular Longhorn feel like a family restaurant. To be honest, my fiancé and I had stopped going there when he left because it just wasn’t the same. We will be putting this Longhorn on our regular rotation list again!

We had been regular diners at the Amherst NH Longhorn for many years, but when they lost their old manager Bill, it felt like any other chain restaurant. We stopped going. Since it had been so long(well over a year).
we decided to stop in. To our Great surprise, Bill was back!

Like he had always done before, Bill made us feel welcome and more like a friend than a customer. We had a great meal and the service was excellent. Now that it feels like a friends place again, instead of a chain restaurant. We will surely be regulars again.

This is the first review I have ever done, truly deserved.

I absolutely love this place!! The manager Bill always takes great care of us, he truly is the best restaurant manager I know. Every time we eat at this location, he personally comes over to our table to see how everything is. For a chain restaurant, he adds a personal touch like no other!!

The food and service have been good for us and you can typically carry on a nice dinner conversation without having to raise your voice. We like Longhorns. We typically order steak tips and I like the wild west shrimp.

Stopped by for a quick bite. Everyone was friendly and the food was great.  We sat near the door and watched them cook our breakfast. Those line cooks had everything down pat and moved through each order quick and efficiently.  Prices were fair. It's a good place to stop if your hungry and need to kill some time.

It's never a bad experience at the Airport Diner! The food is consistently good and they are very quick to serve you. The atmosphere is reminiscent of the 1950s which I personally enjoy. If you're not watching your waistline, I highly recommend getting a malt, they are delicious!! (My favorite is chocolate) The prices are cheap and the portions are big -- what more could you want?
Looks like great family place. Its attached  to holiday inn. Serves all food all day.  Definitely  not a hotel bar.

The Airport Diner is everything good you'd expect from a classic diner. Lots of comfort food offerings, breakfast all day, kitschy (airport themed) decor. One exception is that it is larger than most classic diners. That's a good thing during busy times. 
While they are no longer open 24 hours as they were some time back, 5am to midnight is a pretty generous window to get your grub on. I've enjoyed their breakfasts, burgers, American chop suey and several other faves... all good!
The pricing is very reasonable for the portions. You won't go away hungry and there are take away containers if your eyes are bigger than your belly. Yummy desserts round out the experience. 
Pretty conveniently located on Brown Ave just off Rte 293 with ample free parking. The

They tend to screw your food up pretty often. Have your server read what you ordered back up you before they leave to at least not have it screwed up there. Food is good when you do get it though and the servers aren't rude in the slightest so I can't really get mad at them. I still recommend this place to people though, I just warn them that they might have to do a back and forth to get their food.
